Package: sweep
Type: Package
Title: Tidy Tools for Forecasting
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Date: 2017-06-23
Authors@R: c(
    person("Matt", "Dancho", email = "mdancho@business-science.io", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Davis", "Vaughan", email = "dvaughan@business-science.io", role = c("aut"))
  )
Maintainer: Matt Dancho <mdancho@business-science.io>
Description: 
    `sweep` tidies up the forecasting modeling and prediction workflow. 
    It extends the 'broom' package 
    by providing 'sw_tidy', 'sw_glance', 'sw_augment', and 'sw_tidy_decomp' functions 
    for various forecasting models,
    and it provides the 'sw_sweep' function which converts 'forecast' objects to 
    "tidy" data frames ("tibbles") that can be easily plotted and manipulated.
URL: https://github.com/business-science/sweep
BugReports: https://github.com/business-science/sweep/issues
